                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14583318" author="cziegeler" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2015 12:06:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Neither getRequestURI nor getRequestURL return the decoded string, therefore they are not useful.&lt;br/&gt;
While getServletPath() and getPathInfo() return the decoded values, they don&apos;t include path parameters (like ;v=1.0).&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve now committed a version which:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;uses the decoded values unless the path contains a &quot;;&quot;, in that case getRequestURL is used&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This can only be seen as a temporary solution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems that the Jetty&apos;s servlet implementation does not provide any access to path parameters, therefore I&apos;m wondering why we want to do this? Or maybe I&apos;m overlooking something.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jajans&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jajans&quot;&gt;jajans&lt;/a&gt; What do you think? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14583387" author="cziegeler" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2015 13:35:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Previous versions of the http service did not provide access to this either&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14583556" author="cziegeler" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2015 15:19:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at this, simply using servletPath + pathInfo seems to be the correct thing to do; it&apos;s compatible to what we had before, compatible to what Jetty does, does not introduce any regression. If no one objects I&apos;ll go with that&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14583734" author="jajans" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2015 17:23:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cziegeler&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cziegeler&quot;&gt;cziegeler&lt;/a&gt;: returning the servletPath + pathInfo sounds like the soundest option to me as well...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14584495" author="cziegeler" created="Sat, 13 Jun 2015 07:55:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolved as discussed in rev 1685217&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
